The learners analyse which changes related to teaching methodology and school management, compared to the traditional school, help to supports pupils' readiness for copying with the changing world.
The topics include :
-	characteristics of the changing learning paradigm and how they reveal in Estonian schools;
-	teaching in diverse learning environments;
-	integration between subjects at primary level;
-	project-based learning at primary level;
-	examples of school innovations in Estonia (Open School, Waldorf School , Gaia School, value education schools, entrepreneurial schools, outdoor education schools).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To support future teachers to manage in changing schools and in their future career choices.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The learners -	can make conscious choices for their development and lifelong learning; -	understand what the changing learning paradigm means and how to apply it in practice; -	can compare the characteristics of traditional and changing schools as well as analyse their benefits and drawbacks.
